tive sexual subculture that was tolerated in ways we may find hard to understand. Using letters, diaries, memoirs, police records, novels, and photographs-including sources by the children Douglas encountered-Cleves identifies the cultural practices that structured pedophilic behaviors in England, Italy, and other places Douglas favored. Her book delineates how approaches to adult-child sex have changed over time and offers insight into how society can confront similar scandals today, celebrity and otherwise.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 0aAuthors, EnglishvBiography. 0aSodomyzEngland. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aEngland.  aItaly.  aNorman Douglas.  abiography.  acelebrity.  aintergenerational sex.  aliterature.  apederasty.  apedophilia.  atravel writing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z978311075385108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226733678423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226733678.jpg  a978-3-11-069309-6  UChP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  a978-3-11-075385-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075408-7  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles